llm_verdict.message:
{
  "solution": "Ensure that all user accounts have a non-empty password and that PAM configuration does not allow empty passwords.",
  "steps": [
    "Check /etc/pam.d/system-auth for the nullok option; if present, remove it to prevent empty password authentication.",
    "Verify that pam_unix.so is used in /etc/pam.d/system-auth (without nullok).",
    "List accounts with empty password fields in /etc/passwd: awk -F: '($2 == \"\") {print $1}' /etc/passwd.",
    "For each account identified with an empty password, set a strong password using the passwd command.",
    "Optionally, configure password aging parameters in /etc/login.defs to enforce regular password changes."
  ]
}

